<!-- ==========================================================
(Password Recovery Page)

Description:
Password recovery page template.

This view allows users to request a password reset
by submitting their registered email address.

Responsibilities:
- Render password recovery form.
- Trigger password reset process via frontend logic.
- Provide navigation back to login page.
- Support internationalization for dynamic labels and text.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM naming convention.
- Divided into:
  1. Recovery form section
  2. Navigation link section

Client-Side Behavior:
- Form submission triggers password reset logic (olvidar.js).
- Email input is validated using HTML5 required attribute.
- Reset email dispatch handled via Firebase authentication.

Dependencies:
- olvidar.js
- firebase.js
- auth.js (if required)
- i18n system
- Global bundle.min.js

Security Notes:
- Only email address is collected.
- No password data is processed in this template.
- Reset logic handled securely via Firebase.
- No sensitive operations executed directly in this view.

========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="forgot">
  <h1 class="forgot__title" data-i18n="forgotTitle"></h1>

  <form id="forgot-form" class="forgot__form">
    <label class="forgot__form--label" data-i18n="emailForgot"></label>
    <input id="forgot-email" class="forgot__form--input" type="email" required />
    <button class="forgot__form--submit" type="submit" data-i18n="submitForgot"></button>
  </form>

  <div class="forgot__links">
    <a href="/login" class="forgot__link" data-i18n="backToLogin"></a>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>